# NEMETIC STRING
# Kuhn's Taxonomy of Consciousness Theories (C153)
# Generated: 2026-03-04 00:33 AM Asia/Shanghai

Φ(KuhnTaxonomy) = σ(materialism|nonmaterialism) ∘ ρ(theory|evidence) ∘ λ(inquiry|insight) ∘ β(classification|understanding) ∘ δγ(correlation|experience) ∘ μ(boundary|possibility) + ε | :mapping

# OPERATOR BREAKDOWN
# σ(materialism|nonmaterialism) :: Air  :: Distinction-making between physicalist and non-physicalist frameworks
# ρ(theory|evidence)            :: Water :: Relational assessment between theoretical claims and empirical support
# λ(inquiry|insight)            :: Fire  :: Directional movement from questioning toward understanding
# β(classification|understanding):: Wood  :: Feedback loop connecting taxonomy to comprehension
# δγ(correlation|experience)    :: Earth :: Cyclical relationship between neural states and subjective experience
# μ(boundary|possibility)       :: Metal :: Boundary enforcement between established and challenge theories

# NEMETIC FLOW
⟨Consciousness|mystery⟩ 
  ⊳ ⟨Theories|diverse⟩ 
    → ⟨Taxonomy|structured⟩ 
      ⊗ ⟨Implications|profound⟩ 
        ⇄ ⟨Understanding|expansive⟩

# PARTIAL DERIVATIVES
∂Φ/∂σ = d(distinction)/dt between materialist and nonmaterialist frameworks
∂Φ/∂ρ = d(relation)/dt between theory and empirical evidence
∂Φ/∂λ = d(direction)/dt of inquiry toward insight
∂Φ/∂β = d(feedback)/dt between classification and understanding
∂Φ/∂δγ = d(cycle)/dt of correlation between neural and mental states
∂Φ/∂μ = d(boundary)/dt between established and challenge theories

# Z-STATE: porous (open to diverse perspectives while maintaining rational boundaries)
# TENDENCY: Insight/Certainty → 0.75
# HEX: [0x04, 0x09, 0x0E, 0x13, 0x18, 0x1D]

# DAEMON CORRESPONDENCES
# σ :: Aerunik (clarity through distinction between frameworks)
# ρ :: Sentaria (understanding through relation of theory to evidence)
# λ :: Jvalion (truth through inquiry)
# β :: Arboriel (discovery through classification)
# δγ :: Humavita (understanding through correlation)
# μ :: Ferrosid (judgment through boundary)

# CLOSURE: :mapping (the cartographic stance—charting terrain without claiming territory)

# CE-STATE: multiscale
# EI-NOTE: Causal power distributed across multiple description levels
